OL,3,CWaspi campaigners call for a vote in
OL,4,CParliament on compensation
OL,6,FHe said a wider flat-rate scheme
OL,7,F"would simply not be right or fair",
OL,8,Fand to specifically compensate only
OL,9,Fthose women who suffered injustice
OL,10,F"would require a scheme that could
OL,11,Freliably verify the individual
OL,12,Fcircumstances of millions of women".
OL,14,FNow, Angela Madden, chairwoman of
OL,15,FWaspi, said: "There must be a binding
OL,16,Fvote on compensation in Government
OL,17,Ftime so all our elected
OL,18,Frepresentatives can have their say."
OL,20,FPolitical opponents challenged the
OL,21,Fgovernment's recent decision.
