OL,3,CWaspi campaigners call for a vote in
OL,4,CParliament on compensation
OL,6,FLast week, the Conservatives accused
OL,7,FLabour of "turning against" Waspi
OL,8,Fwomen.
OL,10,FTory MP Mark Garnier said: "If the
OL,11,Fgovernment really believed that these
OL,12,Fwomen had faced a great injustice,
OL,13,Fthey would have found a way to
OL,14,Fcompensate them."
OL,16,FThe Liberal Democrats Work and
OL,17,FPensions spokesman, Steve Darling,
OL,18,Falso criticised the decision, saying
OL,19,Fthe Waspi women will feel "betrayed
OL,20,Fbecause false hope was given to them
OL,21,Fin the autumn".
